**[1846, 09-01] Ms.B.1.6.2.30**

Estlin to May Jr. (bulk in {u}BAA{/u}, No. 222)

Discusses meeting WLG and party for the first time; escorted them to
Bristol for a nice meeting. Wants to form an auxiliary to the League in
Bristol. Regrets that WLG draws so much attention to the divisions in
the antislavery movement. Warns that few influential persons support the
League. “George Thompson’s name carries little weight here. An able man
& excellent speaker, none deny him to be; but he is looked on as a sort
of *adventurer* …”


